OL,3,CGovernment rejects call for public
OL,4,Cinquiry into murder of Sean Brown
OL,6,FThe family of Sean Brown say they are
OL,7,Fdevastated at the Government's
OL,8,Fdecision not to hold a public inquiry
OL,9,Finto the 1997 loyalist murder.
OL,11,FMr Brown was abducted by a Loyalist
OL,12,FVolunteer Force (LVF) gang as he
OL,13,Flocked the gates at Bellaghy Wolfe
OL,14,FTones GAA Club in Co Londonderry.
OL,16,FThe father of six was bundled into the
OL,17,Fboot of his car, taken to Randalstown,
OL,18,FCo Antrim and shot dead. No one has
OL,19,Fever been convicted of his murder.
